  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "H. of Miletus Greek author, 6th cent. BC, on of Hegesander, c. 560-480 BC, first ‘logographer’ 
    (using the term - current since Fr. Creutzer, but somewhat incorrect - for the prose authors before Herodotus), from whom numerous 
    fragments exist (c. 370 in the collection of the FGrH 1). H. is of utmost significance for the development of Greek geography and historiography...." 
    from Meister, Klaus (Berlin). "Hecataeus." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and
